node.text: Suki’s blood test results finally came in yesterday… there is absolutely nothing wrong with her!!! 😭🙏 She is cone free as of today, and is such a happy girl now that she’s all healed up from her abscess. Thanks again to all of you for pouring in your love! It has been a very stressful few weeks, and we are so relieved to know that Suki’s anal gland issue wasn’t caused by any underlying conditions. We will be back to our adventures soon! 😽💓

node.text: Suki is still living the cone life, and she’s definitely “over it” 😹. We are still anxiously waiting on the results of her blood tests, and have our fingers crossed for good news. Hopefully we can get back to our adventures soon, because Suki has been trying to dart out the door any chance she gets! 😸🌼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Suki Cat on July 02, 2021. May be an image of big cat, cat and nature.

node.text:
Suki has been feeling better as each day goes on. 💓 Her wound looks like it’s healing properly, and we have a checkup appointment with our vet in a few days to run some blood tests. Her poops have been small and dry since this all started, which is unusual and concerning. We are hoping for the best.🙏
Thank you so much to all of you for the outpouring of love, advice, and sharing similar experiences. You definitely helped make this whole ordeal a lot less stressful. We are so grateful 😽🧡

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Suki Cat on June 28, 2021. May be a closeup of cat.

node.text:
Poor Suki isn’t doing well. Her condition worsened despite being on antibiotics, and we had to rush her to the vet last night. They drained her abscess and helped relieve some of the pressure from Suki holding in her poop for 3 days. I’m so worried about her, because despite doing everything in our power the first time around it still got worse. Now there is an open wound on her behind and I’m terrified the antibiotics won’t be enough.
It breaks my heart to see her in so much pain. 💔
If any of you have dealt with a ruptured anal gland in your pets before, any advice on keeping her comfortable, keeping the wound clean, or anything else, please let me know in the comments.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Suki Cat on June 26, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Poor Suki ended up at the emergency vet yesterday 😿. She was twitching her backside and seemed super irritated about her butt, upon closer inspection we saw that her behind looked like it had a sore. She got sent home with antibiotics for an infected anal gland, which it turns out is fairly common in cats and dogs. (If your pet seems irritated by something back there, make sure to take a really close look because it was hard to notice!)
Thankfully Suki is in a good mood today, and we will be keeping a very close eye on her until the infection clears up. 🧡
